===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|nedle|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|nædl|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{recons|nēþlō|lang=gem-pro}}, from pre-Germanic {{recons|neh₁-tleh₂|lang=en}}, from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{recons|(s)néh₁|lang=ine-pro}}- ‘to spin, twist’ (compare Dutch {{term|naaien|lang=nl}}, Welsh {{term|nyddu|lang=cy}}, Latin {{term|nere|nēre|lang=la}}, Lithuanian {{term|snaju|snāju|lang=lt}}, Sanskrit {{term||snāyati}} ‘wraps up, winds’). Related to {{l|en|snood}}.

